==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Endearment
<hw>En*dear"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
endearing or the state of being endeared; also, that which manifests,
excites, or increases, affection.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The great
<xex>endearments</xex> of prudent and temperate speech.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her first <qex>endearments</qex> twining round the soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endeavor</ent>⟦br⟧
